Upgrade procedure for mport

Source: https://github.com/midnightbsd/mport.git  (branch: main)

mport is MidnightBSD's own package tool, so the "vendor" upstream is the
MidnightBSD mport repository itself. The vendor branch tracks main directly;
there is no third-party divergence to reconcile.

To upgrade to a new version:

1. Clone the upstream main branch:
     git clone https://github.com/midnightbsd/mport.git
   The version is defined by MPORT_VERSION in libmport/mport_private.h.

2. Use the vendor-update skill:
     vendor branch : vendor/mport
     in-tree prefix: contrib/mport
     tag           : vendor/mport/<version>   (commit msg: "Import mport <version>")

3. rsync the clone (minus .git) into a worktree of vendor/mport, commit, tag,
   then "git subtree merge -P contrib/mport vendor/mport" onto master and each
   stable branch.

There is NO Xlist for mport. Upstream is carried into contrib/mport wholesale
(including any stray upstream artifacts such as replace.patch); prune nothing.

Build-system integration (MidnightBSD-specific, applied on master/stable after
the subtree merge -- these live OUTSIDE contrib/mport and are the only thing
that must be refreshed by hand each import):

  - lib/libmport/Makefile SRCS must list every libmport/*.c that mport builds.
    When upstream adds a new libmport source file, add it to SRCS. Diff the file
    list against the previous import to find additions, e.g.:
       diff <(ls contrib/mport/libmport/*.c | xargs -n1 basename | sort) \
            <(git show vendor/mport/<prev>:libmport/ | ...)
    2.8.0 added: mtree.c, pkgmeta_sort.c, query.c.
  - usr.sbin/mport/Makefile and libexec/mport.*/Makefile normally need no change
    (single-source PROG builds), but re-check if upstream adds files there.

Local patches applied on top of upstream:

  - (none currently) The former MidnightBSD ohash-callback fix in
    libmport/upgrade.c (src commit 526a71f9af, "fix upgrade.c ohash callback
    signatures after ohash update") was folded UPSTREAM as of mport 2.8.0,
    guarded by "#if defined(__MidnightBSD__) && __MidnightBSD_version >= 401002".
    Do NOT re-apply it; upstream now handles both old and new ohash signatures.

Notes:
  - Verify builds after each import: lib/libmport, usr.sbin/mport, libexec/mport.*
  - MPORT_OSVERSION / MPORT_MASTER_VERSION in libmport/mport_private.h are
    maintained upstream (MidnightBSD's own repo), so they carry through the
    vendor import unchanged.
